tl;dr - superior quality Italian that won't break the bank.  Visiting here I heard Baltimore has a Little Italy and knew I had to try a place. My girlfriend decided on this place and at first I was a bit skeptical mostly because there was no other patrons when we arrived shortly after opening (perhaps not many people have time). However I was proven wrong and I was so glad about that.  The interior has a antique charm to it and is well maintained. Although the area ate in was cozy there was another area and possibly an upstairs area.  Our server had a little trouble understanding us but he was very attentive and welcoming providing excellent service.  We ordered an appetizer of lobster raviolis and shared gnocchi in marinara and chicken parmesan. The cream sauce the raviolis sat in was buttery, light and just perfect. The raviolis were nothing short of perfection as well. I could tell they were made from scratch based on the texture and consistency of the pasta. It comes with three pieces priced at $13 but was well worth it. Definitely the best lobster raviolis I've eaten outside Boston.  Possibly just as perfect as the raviolis was the gnocchi and the marinara sauce, both of which are made in-house. I could eat that sauce alone being so flavorful, light, not too sweet, and being a beautiful bright red color. A full serving costs $13 but seems like a steal to me.  The chicken parmesan was very good priced at $13. The breading was excellent and the chicken was juicy. It was served with the same marinara sauce and pasta. Had I only order this I would still be very impressed with the restaurant. As we left the owner, I presume, dressed in a plain white t-shirt and jeans personally asked us if we enjoyed the meal to which I profusely thanked him.  Overall, if you want quality Italian please make a stop to Dalesio's. I will be coming back.

The meal started off well; the garlic bread and bruschetta were fantastic. However, I ordered the pesto gnocchi and the pesto sauce was lacking flavor. The gnocchi itself was cooked well, but the dish just missed the mark.
Dinner was terrible. Chicken parmesan was dry and slightly burnt. Veal saltimbocca was over cooked and disappointing. Will never return will never recommend.

Service was the only reason for 2 stars. We got shrimp scampi and our guest got lasagna.  All dishes came out cold. Lasagna shells were hard with little to no flavor and our shrimp scampi was very bland with an overuse of watery butter. Desserts were cannolis and tiramusu. Cannoli shells were stale with the filling tasting like spoiled milk. Tiramusu was mushy with hardly any coffee flavor. By far the worst ever Italian food I have ever had. I've had better Italian food at a pizza joint. Save your time and money.
Great food
Excellent service & delicious food!
What a great place to eat some good Italian food. Issac made it fun of me and my family. I would definitely recommend this place for everyone.
Atmosphere left a bit to be desired, but the food and services was fantastic
Good food friendly staff
Really good local Italian food. Great seafood inspired dishes.

Little Italy offers plenty of restaurants, go to one of them instead. If I wanted box pasta, and canned sauce (prego?), I would cook at home for a fraction of the cost. As an Italian, this place is an embarrassment. We chose to come here because the balcony looked so pleasant from the outside. While we were there, a fight at Mo's Seafood (restaurant directly beneath the balcony) broke out, there was a lot of screaming, and the cops showed up. NOT a good environment for a relaxing dinner. When we arrived, there was no silverware on the tables, we received bread with not napkins or plates... and again when the food came out, it was a sad excuse of italian food. Terrible service, terrible location, terrible food. AVOID IT AT ALL COSTS.

There are plenty of Italian restaurants to choose from in little Italy so you better be good. Dalesio's was a solid good and I would return. I started with their gorgonzola dressed salad. It was just okay and lacked much visual presentation. The dressing was decent but overwhelmed the salad.  My entree was the highlight. Calamari in marinating with spaghetti. The sauce was delicious and the squid cooked acceptably.  The service was friendly, courteous, professional and attentive. A very nice experience.
This is an all around great place! Make sure you get David as your server. he was wonderful!

We just had our mother's 70th birthday party at Dalesio's. 19 adults plus 4 children. It was an outstanding experience. Mr. Paul Oliver was my contact from the restaurant who helped to coordinate the event. It was very easy to plan, he asked all the right questions on how to set up the party. Everything went extremely well. The appetizers and wine were ready when everyone showed up.  The wine was outstanding and flowed well. The pace of the evening was great. We were not rushed. Everyone enjoyed themselves. The food came out at appropriate times and temperature. And the food was OUTSTANDING. I hate to put this online, but the food is incredible for the price you pay. You cannot get a better value for your money in Little Italy. We are already planning on when we will go back!
Got kicked out because I wasn't wearing a suit.  I also got told I wouldn't be able to afford this restaurant.
The best Italian food I have had by far! The service was great. You must try the limoncello.cake and chocolate martini .. It is phenomenal! !
Outstanding!!!!

Still remember the near-magical experience one perfect-weather weekday evening during the 2001/2 Volvo Ocean Race. Dalesio's owner picked up a client and me from the Hyatt Inner Harbor in a big clean van. We enjoyed his commentary on the history, scenery and, especially, the enthusiastic Italian greetings and waves exchanged between him and residents of Little Italy as we drove slowly to the restaurant. Perfect service. Wonderful food. Forever smiles!
Delicious vitello frances and amazing tiramisu! Definitely worth your money GO! GO! GO! GO!
Good food.
The waiter was great and very friendly.  The food was good and the place had great atmosphere. Ask for David, he took very good care of us!
Nice restaurant , good taste and fresh Friendly staff love it

Reading the menu on the street, Isaac came out and greeted us, made jokes, told us our table was ready. Came in and spent the next 2.5 hours enjoying great food, great service and wonderful ambience. Everything was perfect - the creme brulee was to DIE FOR! Then took a selfie on the street with Isaac again!  Wish I could give it more than 5 stars!
Worst experience ever
A real treat to go back after 18 years. Great food and service. A "feel good" place to eat. Not the Ritz... just good old fashioned friendly service and a satisfying Italian meal!

My wife and I had dinner on the balcony here last night.... As we were seated we heard a local couple tell the waiter they just had the best crab cakes in Baltimore.  Good prompt service made a good first impression.  We ordered the shrimp and crab meat ravioli app. before ordering our main courses to taste the quality of food.  The fresh seafood wrapped in homemade pasta topped with an awesome creamy tomato and basil sauce was delicious.  We decide to stay. My wife absolutely loved her lasagna and I really enjoyed the veal bolognese over linguini.  We are usually disappointed dining out bc my wife honestly cooks better meals then most chefs but We were impressed.  When you are wiping the sauces off your plate and the plate next too you with their homemade bread to savory every last bite: You will be happy you dined here!
Our dinner was very good. The service was OK...just a little slow.

Went in for an early dinner, service was very welcoming and sat us immediately. We had stopped by the night before to look at a menu, chose to go somewhere else, however we were remembered the next night. Ordered a appetizer, the vegetable soup with Maryland crab, very large portion size and quite delicious. Had three different entrees, one seafood, one vegetarian, and one veal - all very delicious. Had a great dessert (panacotta) with wonderful espresso. Would return and recommend to friends!
